{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012SBSAG9citCjkNNsLRCX3X","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 6-2: Verify Stream-JSON Pipeline End-to-End\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Goal\n     6→Prove the full data flow works: Claude stream-json → ralph tee → Node.js handler → Ink renderer. Add an E2E test that pipes real NDJSON through the full pipeline and asserts the renderer receives correct events.\n     7→\n     8→## Context\n     9→The pipeline has never been tested end-to-end. Each layer has unit tests but no integration test confirms data flows from ralph's stdout through to the Ink renderer in real-time. Potential issues: tee buffering in pipe mode, NDJSON line splitting across chunk boundaries, thinking_delta events polluting the stream.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Integration test pipes a recorded NDJSON file (from `ralph/logs/`) through the full `makeLineHandler → parseStreamLine → rendererHandle.update` chain\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Test asserts tool-start, tool-input, tool-complete, text events reach the renderer in correct order\n    15→- [ ] AC3: Test confirms thinking_delta, hook_started, hook_response, init events are silently ignored (not errors)\n    16→- [ ] AC4: Test confirms ralph stderr messages (`[SUCCESS]`, `[WARN]`, `[LOOP]`) are parsed into StoryMessage objects\n    17→- [ ] AC5: Manual verification: run `codeharness run`, let it execute 1 story, confirm tool calls and thoughts appear in real-time (document with screenshot in proof)\n    18→\n    19→## Files to Change\n    20→- `tests/run-pipeline.test.ts` — new integration test\n    21→- `tests/fixtures/sample-stream.ndjson` — recorded fixture from real session\n    22→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0131GHuAW486cLBuPTkCgMF4","session_id":"eb26302c-c52a-41c7-9204-5eb8c12a854c","uuid":"49b9234c-d197-48ba-87ed-5bc7a1d4950c","timestamp":"2026-03-21T11:15:20.978Z"}
