{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0131GHuAW486cLBuPTkCgMF4","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file updated at `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/6-2-verify-stream-json-pipeline-e2e.md`.\n\nChanges made:\n- Status changed from `backlog` to `in-progress`\n- Added user story format (\"As a developer...\")\n- Appended `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` to AC1-AC4 (all test-based, runnable via `npm test` or similar)\n- Appended `<!-- verification: integration-required -->` to AC5 (requires running `codeharness run` against a real story with visual confirmation and screenshot)\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- No epic-6 definition file exists separately (only a retrospective). The story file already existed with sufficient detail, so this was not blocking.\n\n**Workarounds applied:**\n- None.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- AC5 requires manual verification with a screenshot as proof. This is inherently non-automatable and depends on having a valid story in backlog to execute against. It may be hard to reproduce in CI.\n- AC1 references `ralph/logs/` for recorded NDJSON — those log files are gitignored/ephemeral. The fixture (`tests/fixtures/sample-stream.ndjson`) needs to be created by hand-curating a real log, which is a prerequisite not tracked anywhere.\n- The story references `rendererHandle.update` — if the renderer API changed during story 6-1, these test assumptions may be stale.\n\n**Observations:**\n- This is the last story in Epic 6. Completing it would close the epic.\n- AC1-AC4 form a clean, automatable integration test suite. AC5 is the only outlier requiring human interaction."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aa7030d32294ab446 (use SendMessage with to: 'aa7030d32294ab446' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 16185\ntool_uses: 12\nduration_ms: 65824</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eb26302c-c52a-41c7-