{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011MZCNq82wSd9DbtyWLrygs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 6-2: Verify Stream-JSON Pipeline End-to-End\n     2→\n     3→## Status: in-progress\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer maintaining codeharness,\n     8→I want an end-to-end integration test for the stream-JSON pipeline,\n     9→so that I can confidently refactor any layer knowing the full data flow is validated.\n    10→\n    11→## Goal\n    12→\n    13→Prove the full data flow works: Claude stream-json → ralph tee → Node.js handler → Ink renderer. Add an E2E test that pipes real NDJSON through the full pipeline and asserts the renderer receives correct events.\n    14→\n    15→## Context\n    16→\n    17→The pipeline has never been tested end-to-end. Each layer has unit tests but no integration test confirms data flows from ralph's stdout through to the Ink renderer in real-time. Potential issues: tee buffering in pipe mode, NDJSON line splitting across chunk boundaries, thinking_delta events polluting the stream.\n    18→\n    19→## Acceptance Criteria\n    20→\n    21→- [ ] AC1: Integration test pipes a recorded NDJSON file (from `ralph/logs/`) through the full `makeLineHandler → parseStreamLine → rendererHandle.update` chain <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→- [ ] AC2: Test asserts tool-start, tool-input, tool-complete, text events reach the renderer in correct order <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→- [ ] AC3: Test confirms thinking_delta, hook_started, hook_response, init events are silently ignored (not errors) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→- [ ] AC4: Test confirms ralph stderr messages (`[SUCCESS]`, `[WARN]`, `[LOOP]`) are parsed into StoryMessage objects <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25→- [ ] AC5: Manual verification: run `codeharness run`, let it execute 1 story, confirm tool calls and thoughts appear in real-time (document with screenshot in proof) <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n    26→\n    27→## Files to Change\n    28→\n    29→- `tests/run-pipeline.test.ts` — new integration test\n    30→- `tests/fixtures/sample-stream.ndjson` — recorded fixture from real session\n    31→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eb26302c-c52a-41c7-9204-5eb8c12a854c","uuid":"6b7a942c-ff90-4ec1-9b3a-f2a8b1b58723","timestamp":"2026-03-21T11:16:17.728Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/6-2-verify-stream-json-pipeline-e2e.md","content":"# Story 6-2: Verify Stream-JSON Pipeline End-to-End\n\n## Status: in-progress\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer maintaining codeharness,\nI want an end-to-end integration test for the stream-JSON pipeline,\nso that I can confidently refactor any layer knowing the full data flow is validated.\n\n## Goal\n\nProve the full data flow works: Claude stream-json → ralph tee → Node.js handler → Ink renderer. Add an E2E test that pipes real NDJSON through the full pipeline and asserts the renderer receives correct events.\n\n## Context\n\nThe pipeline has never been tested end-to-end. Each layer has unit tests but no integration test confirms data flows from ralph's stdout through to the Ink renderer in real-time. Potential issues: tee buffering in pipe mode, NDJSON line splitting across chunk boundaries, thinking_delta events polluting the stream.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC1: Integration test pipes a recorded NDJSON file (from `ralph/logs/`) through the full `makeLineHandler → parseStreamLine → rendererHandle.update` chain <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC2: Test asserts tool-start, tool-input, tool-complete, text events reach the renderer in correct order <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC3: Test confirms thinking_delta, hook_started, hook_response, init events are silently ignored (not errors) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC4: Test confirms ralph stderr messages (`[SUCCESS]`, `[WARN]`, `[LOOP]`) are parsed into StoryMessage objects <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC5: Manual verification: run `codeharness run`, let it execute 1 story, confirm tool calls and thoughts appear in real-time (document with screenshot in proof) <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n\n## Files to Change\n\n- `tests/run-pipeline.test.ts` — new integration test\n- `tests/fixtures/sample-stream.ndjson` — recorded fixture from real session\n","numLines":31,"startLine":1,"totalLines":31}}}
