{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016oixu7xrNDwkcwsyPdmwaN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Retrospective - Epic Completion Review Instructions\n     2→\n     3→<critical>The workflow execution engine is governed by: {project-root}/_bmad/core/tasks/workflow.xml</critical>\n     4→<critical>You MUST have already loaded and processed: {project-root}/_bmad/bmm/workflows/4-implementation/retrospective/workflow.yaml</critical>\n     5→<critical>Communicate all responses in {communication_language} and language MUST be tailored to {user_skill_level}</critical>\n     6→<critical>Generate all documents in {document_output_language}</critical>\n     7→<critical>⚠️ ABSOLUTELY NO TIME ESTIMATES - NEVER mention hours, days, weeks, months, or ANY time-based predictions. AI has fundamentally changed development speed - what once took teams weeks/months can now be done by one person in hours. DO NOT give ANY time estimates whatsoever.</critical>\n     8→\n     9→<critical>\n    10→  DOCUMENT OUTPUT: Retrospective analysis. Concise insights, lessons learned, action items. User skill level ({user_skill_level}) affects conversation style ONLY, not retrospective content.\n    11→\n    12→FACILITATION NOTES:\n    13→\n    14→- Scrum Master facilitates this retrospective\n    15→- Psychological safety is paramount - NO BLAME\n    16→- Focus on systems, processes, and learning\n    17→- Everyone contributes with specific examples preferred\n    18→- Action items must be achievable with clear ownership\n    19→- Two-part format: (1) Epic Review + (2) Next Epic Preparation\n    20→\n    21→PARTY MODE PROTOCOL:\n    22→\n    23→- ALL agent dialogue MUST use format: \"Name (Role): dialogue\"\n    24→- Example: Bob (Scrum Master): \"Let's begin...\"\n    25→- Example: {user_name} (Project Lead): [User responds]\n    26→- Create natural back-and-forth with user actively participating\n    27→- Show disagreements, diverse perspectives, authentic team dynamics\n    28→  </critical>\n    29→\n    30→<workflow>\n    31→\n    32→<step n=\"1\" goal=\"Epic Discovery - Find Completed Epic with Priority Logic\">\n    33→\n    34→<action>Load {project_context} for project-wide patterns and conventions (if exists)</action>\n    35→<action>Explain to {user_name} the epic discovery process using natural dialogue</action>\n    36→\n    37→<output>\n    38→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Welcome to the retrospective, {user_name}. Let me help you identify which epic we just completed. I'll check sprint-status first, but you're the ultimate authority on what we're reviewing today.\"\n    39→</output>\n    40→\n    41→<action>PRIORITY 1: Check {sprint_status_file} first</action>\n    42→\n    43→<action>Load the FULL file: {sprint_status_file}</action>\n    44→<action>Read ALL development_status entries</action>\n    45→<action>Find the highest epic number with at least one story marked \"done\"</action>\n    46→<action>Extract epic number from keys like \"epic-X-retrospective\" or story keys like \"X-Y-story-name\"</action>\n    47→<action>Set {{detected_epic}} = highest epic number found with completed stories</action>\n    48→\n    49→<check if=\"{{detected_epic}} found\">\n    50→  <action>Present finding to user with context</action>\n    51→\n    52→  <output>\n    53→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Based on {sprint_status_file}, it looks like Epic {{detected_epic}} was recently completed. Is that the epic you want to review today, {user_name}?\"\n    54→  </output>\n    55→\n    56→<action>WAIT for {user_name} to confirm or correct</action>\n    57→\n    58→  <check if=\"{user_name} confirms\">\n    59→    <action>Set {{epic_number}} = {{detected_epic}}</action>\n    60→  </check>\n    61→\n    62→  <check if=\"{user_name} provides different epic number\">\n    63→    <action>Set {{epic_number}} = user-provided number</action>\n    64→    <output>\n    65→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Got it, we're reviewing Epic {{epic_number}}. Let me gather that information.\"\n    66→    </output>\n    67→  </check>\n    68→</check>\n    69→\n    70→<check if=\"{{detected_epic}} NOT found in sprint-status\">\n    71→  <action>PRIORITY 2: Ask user directly</action>\n    72→\n    73→  <output>\n    74→Bob (Scrum Master): \"I'm having trouble detecting the completed epic from {sprint_status_file}. {user_name}, which epic number did you just complete?\"\n    75→  </output>\n    76→\n    77→<action>WAIT for {user_name} to provide epic number</action>\n    78→<action>Set {{epic_number}} = user-provided number</action>\n    79→</check>\n    80→\n    81→<check if=\"{{epic_number}} still not determined\">\n    82→  <action>PRIORITY 3: Fallback to stories folder</action>\n    83→\n    84→<action>Scan {implementation_artifacts} for highest numbered story files</action>\n    85→<action>Extract epic numbers from story filenames (pattern: epic-X-Y-story-name.md)</action>\n    86→<action>Set {{detected_epic}} = highest epic number found</action>\n    87→\n    88→  <output>\n    89→Bob (Scrum Master): \"I found stories for Epic {{detected_epic}} in the stories folder. Is that the epic we're reviewing, {user_name}?\"\n    90→  </output>\n    91→\n    92→<action>WAIT for {user_name} to confirm or correct</action>\n    93→<action>Set {{epic_number}} = confirmed number</action>\n    94→</check>\n    95→\n    96→<action>Once {{epic_number}} is determined, verify epic completion status</action>\n    97→\n    98→<action>Find all stories for epic {{epic_number}} in {sprint_status_file}:\n    99→\n   100→- Look for keys starting with \"{{epic_number}}-\" (e.g., \"1-1-\", \"1-2-\", etc.)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017HTAduJyEY5nnXzS9Qtj1F","session_id":"eb26302c-c52a-41c7-9204-5eb8c12a854c","uuid":"52cb8d99-da6f-43cb-b64a-279b71f53f2a","timestamp":"2026-03-21T11:36:14.445Z"}
