{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01X2cYV5DVfQfY6JAmMmKveN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LEF9CfytzR8L2Q4wNqJPeJ","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad/bmm/workflows/4-implementation/retrospective/instructions.md","offset":200,"limit":200},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1609,"cache_read_input_tokens":13973,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1609,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017HTAduJyEY5nnXzS9Qtj1F","session_id":"eb26302c-c52a-41c7-9204-5eb8c12a854c","uuid":"e370f0c7-0cc6-4ba6-8ea2-51f532db9092"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LEF9CfytzR8L2Q4wNqJPeJ","type":"tool_result","content":"   200→- Track successful experiments or approaches\n   201→\n   202→**Technical Debt Incurred:**\n   203→\n   204→- Look for \"## Technical Debt\", \"## TODO\", \"## Known Issues\", \"## Future Work\" sections\n   205→- Document shortcuts taken and why\n   206→- Track debt items that affect next epic\n   207→- Note severity and priority of debt items\n   208→\n   209→**Testing and Quality Insights:**\n   210→\n   211→- Look for \"## Testing\", \"## QA Notes\", \"## Test Results\" sections\n   212→- Note testing challenges or surprises\n   213→- Track bug patterns or regression issues\n   214→- Document test coverage gaps\n   215→\n   216→<action>Synthesize patterns across all stories:</action>\n   217→\n   218→**Common Struggles:**\n   219→\n   220→- Identify issues that appeared in 2+ stories (e.g., \"3 out of 5 stories had API authentication issues\")\n   221→- Note areas where team consistently struggled\n   222→- Track where complexity was underestimated\n   223→\n   224→**Recurring Review Feedback:**\n   225→\n   226→- Identify feedback themes (e.g., \"Error handling was flagged in every review\")\n   227→- Note quality patterns (positive and negative)\n   228→- Track areas where team improved over the course of epic\n   229→\n   230→**Breakthrough Moments:**\n   231→\n   232→- Document key discoveries (e.g., \"Story 3 discovered the caching pattern we used for rest of epic\")\n   233→- Note when team velocity improved dramatically\n   234→- Track innovative solutions worth repeating\n   235→\n   236→**Velocity Patterns:**\n   237→\n   238→- Calculate average completion time per story\n   239→- Note velocity trends (e.g., \"First 2 stories took 3x longer than estimated\")\n   240→- Identify which types of stories went faster/slower\n   241→\n   242→**Team Collaboration Highlights:**\n   243→\n   244→- Note moments of excellent collaboration mentioned in stories\n   245→- Track where pair programming or mob programming was effective\n   246→- Document effective problem-solving sessions\n   247→\n   248→<action>Store this synthesis - these patterns will drive the retrospective discussion</action>\n   249→\n   250→<output>\n   251→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Okay, I've reviewed all {{total_stories}} story records. I found some really interesting patterns we should discuss.\"\n   252→\n   253→Dana (QA Engineer): \"I'm curious what you found, Bob. I noticed some things in my testing too.\"\n   254→\n   255→Bob (Scrum Master): \"We'll get to all of it. But first, let me load the previous epic's retro to see if we learned from last time.\"\n   256→</output>\n   257→\n   258→</step>\n   259→\n   260→<step n=\"3\" goal=\"Load and Integrate Previous Epic Retrospective\">\n   261→\n   262→<action>Calculate previous epic number: {{prev_epic_num}} = {{epic_number}} - 1</action>\n   263→\n   264→<check if=\"{{prev_epic_num}} >= 1\">\n   265→  <action>Search for previous retrospectives using pattern: {implementation_artifacts}/epic-{{prev_epic_num}}-retro-*.md</action>\n   266→\n   267→  <check if=\"previous retrospectives found\">\n   268→    <output>\n   269→Bob (Scrum Master): \"I found our retrospectives from Epic {{prev_epic_num}}. Let me see what we committed to back then...\"\n   270→    </output>\n   271→\n   272→    <action>Read the previous retrospectives</action>\n   273→\n   274→    <action>Extract key elements:</action>\n   275→    - **Action items committed**: What did the team agree to improve?\n   276→    - **Lessons learned**: What insights were captured?\n   277→    - **Process improvements**: What changes were agreed upon?\n   278→    - **Technical debt flagged**: What debt was documented?\n   279→    - **Team agreements**: What commitments were made?\n   280→    - **Preparation tasks**: What was needed for this epic?\n   281→\n   282→    <action>Cross-reference with current epic execution:</action>\n   283→\n   284→    **Action Item Follow-Through:**\n   285→    - For each action item from Epic {{prev_epic_num}} retro, check if it was completed\n   286→    - Look for evidence in current epic's story records\n   287→    - Mark each action item: ✅ Completed, ⏳ In Progress, ❌ Not Addressed\n   288→\n   289→    **Lessons Applied:**\n   290→    - For each lesson from Epic {{prev_epic_num}}, check if team applied it in Epic {{epic_number}}\n   291→    - Look for evidence in dev notes, review feedback, or outcomes\n   292→    - Document successes and missed opportunities\n   293→\n   294→    **Process Improvements Effectiveness:**\n   295→    - For each process change agreed to in Epic {{prev_epic_num}}, assess if it helped\n   296→    - Did the change improve velocity, quality, or team satisfaction?\n   297→    - Should we keep, modify, or abandon the change?\n   298→\n   299→    **Technical Debt Status:**\n   300→    - For each debt item from Epic {{prev_epic_num}}, check if it was addressed\n   301→    - Did unaddressed debt cause problems in Epic {{epic_number}}?\n   302→    - Did the debt grow or shrink?\n   303→\n   304→    <action>Prepare \"continuity insights\" for the retrospective discussion</action>\n   305→\n   306→    <action>Identify wins where previous lessons were applied successfully:</action>\n   307→    - Document specific examples of applied learnings\n   308→    - Note positive impact on Epic {{epic_number}} outcomes\n   309→    - Celebrate team growth and improvement\n   310→\n   311→    <action>Identify missed opportunities where previous lessons were ignored:</action>\n   312→    - Document where team repeated previous mistakes\n   313→    - Note impact of not applying lessons (without blame)\n   314→    - Explore barriers that prevented application\n   315→\n   316→    <output>\n   317→\n   318→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Interesting... in Epic {{prev_epic_num}}'s retro, we committed to {{action_count}} action items.\"\n   319→\n   320→Alice (Product Owner): \"How'd we do on those, Bob?\"\n   321→\n   322→Bob (Scrum Master): \"We completed {{completed_count}}, made progress on {{in_progress_count}}, but didn't address {{not_addressed_count}}.\"\n   323→\n   324→Charlie (Senior Dev): _looking concerned_ \"Which ones didn't we address?\"\n   325→\n   326→Bob (Scrum Master): \"We'll discuss that in the retro. Some of them might explain challenges we had this epic.\"\n   327→\n   328→Elena (Junior Dev): \"That's... actually pretty insightful.\"\n   329→\n   330→Bob (Scrum Master): \"That's why we track this stuff. Pattern recognition helps us improve.\"\n   331→</output>\n   332→\n   333→  </check>\n   334→\n   335→  <check if=\"no previous retro found\">\n   336→    <output>\n   337→Bob (Scrum Master): \"I don't see a retrospective for Epic {{prev_epic_num}}. Either we skipped it, or this is your first retro.\"\n   338→\n   339→Alice (Product Owner): \"Probably our first one. Good time to start the habit!\"\n   340→</output>\n   341→<action>Set {{first_retrospective}} = true</action>\n   342→</check>\n   343→</check>\n   344→\n   345→<check if=\"{{prev_epic_num}} < 1\">\n   346→  <output>\n   347→Bob (Scrum Master): \"This is Epic 1, so naturally there's no previous retro to reference. We're starting fresh!\"\n   348→\n   349→Charlie (Senior Dev): \"First epic, first retro. Let's make it count.\"\n   350→</output>\n   351→<action>Set {{first_retrospective}} = true</action>\n   352→</check>\n   353→\n   354→</step>\n   355→\n   356→<step n=\"4\" goal=\"Preview Next Epic with Change Detection\">\n   357→\n   358→<action>Calculate next epic number: {{next_epic_num}} = {{epic_number}} + 1</action>\n   359→\n   360→<output>\n   361→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Before we dive into the discussion, let me take a quick look at Epic {{next_epic_num}} to understand what's coming.\"\n   362→\n   363→Alice (Product Owner): \"Good thinking - helps us connect what we learned to what we're about to do.\"\n   364→</output>\n   365→\n   366→<action>Attempt to load next epic using selective loading strategy:</action>\n   367→\n   368→**Try sharded first (more specific):**\n   369→<action>Check if file exists: {planning_artifacts}/epic*/epic-{{next_epic_num}}.md</action>\n   370→\n   371→<check if=\"sharded epic file found\">\n   372→  <action>Load {planning_artifacts}/*epic*/epic-{{next_epic_num}}.md</action>\n   373→  <action>Set {{next_epic_source}} = \"sharded\"</action>\n   374→</check>\n   375→\n   376→**Fallback to whole document:**\n   377→<check if=\"sharded epic not found\">\n   378→<action>Check if file exists: {planning_artifacts}/epic*.md</action>\n   379→\n   380→  <check if=\"whole epic file found\">\n   381→    <action>Load entire epics document</action>\n   382→    <action>Extract Epic {{next_epic_num}} section</action>\n   383→    <action>Set {{next_epic_source}} = \"whole\"</action>\n   384→  </check>\n   385→</check>\n   386→\n   387→<check if=\"next epic found\">\n   388→  <action>Analyze next epic for:</action>\n   389→  - Epic title and objectives\n   390→  - Planned stories and complexity estimates\n   391→  - Dependencies on Epic {{epic_number}} work\n   392→  - New technical requirements or capabilities needed\n   393→  - Potential risks or unknowns\n   394→  - Business goals and success criteria\n   395→\n   396→<action>Identify dependencies on completed work:</action>\n   397→\n   398→- What components from Epic {{epic_number}} does Epic {{next_epic_num}} rely on?\n   399→- Are all prerequisites complete and stable?"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017HTAduJyEY5nnXzS9Qtj1F","session_id":"eb26302c-c52a-41c7-9204-5eb8c12a854c","uuid":"10c1f7cf-af07-4cda-8fbe-871bd4f5c513","timestamp":"2026-03-21T11:36:24.980Z"}
