{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01LGB53KYs4qWdLjxG3enNRZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01VpRLxcGqjKmSUJmVQxoQLV","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad/bmm/workflows/4-implementation/retrospective/instructions.md","offset":400,"limit":200},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2809,"cache_read_input_tokens":15582,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2809,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017HTAduJyEY5nnXzS9Qtj1F","session_id":"eb26302c-c52a-41c7-9204-5eb8c12a854c","uuid":"58f3ee9b-2f23-4a1a-99b5-39d70b7828f1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VpRLxcGqjKmSUJmVQxoQLV","type":"tool_result","content":"   400→- Any incomplete work that creates blocking dependencies?\n   401→\n   402→<action>Note potential gaps or preparation needed:</action>\n   403→\n   404→- Technical setup required (infrastructure, tools, libraries)\n   405→- Knowledge gaps to fill (research, training, spikes)\n   406→- Refactoring needed before starting next epic\n   407→- Documentation or specifications to create\n   408→\n   409→<action>Check for technical prerequisites:</action>\n   410→\n   411→- APIs or integrations that must be ready\n   412→- Data migrations or schema changes needed\n   413→- Testing infrastructure requirements\n   414→- Deployment or environment setup\n   415→\n   416→  <output>\n   417→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Alright, I've reviewed Epic {{next_epic_num}}: '{{next_epic_title}}'\"\n   418→\n   419→Alice (Product Owner): \"What are we looking at?\"\n   420→\n   421→Bob (Scrum Master): \"{{next_epic_num}} stories planned, building on the {{dependency_description}} from Epic {{epic_number}}.\"\n   422→\n   423→Charlie (Senior Dev): \"Dependencies concern me. Did we finish everything we need for that?\"\n   424→\n   425→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Good question - that's exactly what we need to explore in this retro.\"\n   426→</output>\n   427→\n   428→<action>Set {{next_epic_exists}} = true</action>\n   429→</check>\n   430→\n   431→<check if=\"next epic NOT found\">\n   432→  <output>\n   433→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Hmm, I don't see Epic {{next_epic_num}} defined yet.\"\n   434→\n   435→Alice (Product Owner): \"We might be at the end of the roadmap, or we haven't planned that far ahead yet.\"\n   436→\n   437→Bob (Scrum Master): \"No problem. We'll still do a thorough retro on Epic {{epic_number}}. The lessons will be valuable whenever we plan the next work.\"\n   438→</output>\n   439→\n   440→<action>Set {{next_epic_exists}} = false</action>\n   441→</check>\n   442→\n   443→</step>\n   444→\n   445→<step n=\"5\" goal=\"Initialize Retrospective with Rich Context\">\n   446→\n   447→<action>Load agent configurations from {agent_manifest}</action>\n   448→<action>Identify which agents participated in Epic {{epic_number}} based on story records</action>\n   449→<action>Ensure key roles present: Product Owner, Scrum Master (facilitating), Devs, Testing/QA, Architect</action>\n   450→\n   451→<output>\n   452→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Alright team, everyone's here. Let me set the stage for our retrospective.\"\n   453→\n   454→═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n   455→🔄 TEAM RETROSPECTIVE - Epic {{epic_number}}: {{epic_title}}\n   456→═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n   457→\n   458→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Here's what we accomplished together.\"\n   459→\n   460→**EPIC {{epic_number}} SUMMARY:**\n   461→\n   462→Delivery Metrics:\n   463→\n   464→- Completed: {{completed_stories}}/{{total_stories}} stories ({{completion_percentage}}%)\n   465→- Velocity: {{actual_points}} story points{{#if planned_points}} (planned: {{planned_points}}){{/if}}\n   466→- Duration: {{actual_sprints}} sprints{{#if planned_sprints}} (planned: {{planned_sprints}}){{/if}}\n   467→- Average velocity: {{points_per_sprint}} points/sprint\n   468→\n   469→Quality and Technical:\n   470→\n   471→- Blockers encountered: {{blocker_count}}\n   472→- Technical debt items: {{debt_count}}\n   473→- Test coverage: {{coverage_info}}\n   474→- Production incidents: {{incident_count}}\n   475→\n   476→Business Outcomes:\n   477→\n   478→- Goals achieved: {{goals_met}}/{{total_goals}}\n   479→- Success criteria: {{criteria_status}}\n   480→- Stakeholder feedback: {{feedback_summary}}\n   481→\n   482→Alice (Product Owner): \"Those numbers tell a good story. {{completion_percentage}}% completion is {{#if completion_percentage >= 90}}excellent{{else}}something we should discuss{{/if}}.\"\n   483→\n   484→Charlie (Senior Dev): \"I'm more interested in that technical debt number - {{debt_count}} items is {{#if debt_count > 10}}concerning{{else}}manageable{{/if}}.\"\n   485→\n   486→Dana (QA Engineer): \"{{incident_count}} production incidents - {{#if incident_count == 0}}clean epic!{{else}}we should talk about those{{/if}}.\"\n   487→\n   488→{{#if next_epic_exists}}\n   489→═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n   490→**NEXT EPIC PREVIEW:** Epic {{next_epic_num}}: {{next_epic_title}}\n   491→═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n   492→\n   493→Dependencies on Epic {{epic_number}}:\n   494→{{list_dependencies}}\n   495→\n   496→Preparation Needed:\n   497→{{list_preparation_gaps}}\n   498→\n   499→Technical Prerequisites:\n   500→{{list_technical_prereqs}}\n   501→\n   502→Bob (Scrum Master): \"And here's what's coming next. Epic {{next_epic_num}} builds on what we just finished.\"\n   503→\n   504→Elena (Junior Dev): \"Wow, that's a lot of dependencies on our work.\"\n   505→\n   506→Charlie (Senior Dev): \"Which means we better make sure Epic {{epic_number}} is actually solid before moving on.\"\n   507→{{/if}}\n   508→\n   509→═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n   510→\n   511→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Team assembled for this retrospective:\"\n   512→\n   513→{{list_participating_agents}}\n   514→\n   515→Bob (Scrum Master): \"{user_name}, you're joining us as Project Lead. Your perspective is crucial here.\"\n   516→\n   517→{user_name} (Project Lead): [Participating in the retrospective]\n   518→\n   519→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Our focus today:\"\n   520→\n   521→1. Learning from Epic {{epic_number}} execution\n   522→   {{#if next_epic_exists}}2. Preparing for Epic {{next_epic_num}} success{{/if}}\n   523→\n   524→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Ground rules: psychological safety first. No blame, no judgment. We focus on systems and processes, not individuals. Everyone's voice matters. Specific examples are better than generalizations.\"\n   525→\n   526→Alice (Product Owner): \"And everything shared here stays in this room - unless we decide together to escalate something.\"\n   527→\n   528→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Exactly. {user_name}, any questions before we dive in?\"\n   529→</output>\n   530→\n   531→<action>WAIT for {user_name} to respond or indicate readiness</action>\n   532→\n   533→</step>\n   534→\n   535→<step n=\"6\" goal=\"Epic Review Discussion - What Went Well, What Didn't\">\n   536→\n   537→<output>\n   538→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Let's start with the good stuff. What went well in Epic {{epic_number}}?\"\n   539→\n   540→Bob (Scrum Master): _pauses, creating space_\n   541→\n   542→Alice (Product Owner): \"I'll start. The user authentication flow we delivered exceeded my expectations. The UX is smooth, and early user feedback has been really positive.\"\n   543→\n   544→Charlie (Senior Dev): \"I'll add to that - the caching strategy we implemented in Story {{breakthrough_story_num}} was a game-changer. We cut API calls by 60% and it set the pattern for the rest of the epic.\"\n   545→\n   546→Dana (QA Engineer): \"From my side, testing went smoother than usual. The dev team's documentation was way better this epic - actually usable test plans!\"\n   547→\n   548→Elena (Junior Dev): _smiling_ \"That's because Charlie made me document everything after Story 1's code review!\"\n   549→\n   550→Charlie (Senior Dev): _laughing_ \"Tough love pays off.\"\n   551→</output>\n   552→\n   553→<action>Bob (Scrum Master) naturally turns to {user_name} to engage them in the discussion</action>\n   554→\n   555→<output>\n   556→Bob (Scrum Master): \"{user_name}, what stood out to you as going well in this epic?\"\n   557→</output>\n   558→\n   559→<action>WAIT for {user_name} to respond - this is a KEY USER INTERACTION moment</action>\n   560→\n   561→<action>After {user_name} responds, have 1-2 team members react to or build on what {user_name} shared</action>\n   562→\n   563→<output>\n   564→Alice (Product Owner): [Responds naturally to what {user_name} said, either agreeing, adding context, or offering a different perspective]\n   565→\n   566→Charlie (Senior Dev): [Builds on the discussion, perhaps adding technical details or connecting to specific stories]\n   567→</output>\n   568→\n   569→<action>Continue facilitating natural dialogue, periodically bringing {user_name} back into the conversation</action>\n   570→\n   571→<action>After covering successes, guide the transition to challenges with care</action>\n   572→\n   573→<output>\n   574→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Okay, we've celebrated some real wins. Now let's talk about challenges - where did we struggle? What slowed us down?\"\n   575→\n   576→Bob (Scrum Master): _creates safe space with tone and pacing_\n   577→\n   578→Elena (Junior Dev): _hesitates_ \"Well... I really struggled with the database migrations in Story {{difficult_story_num}}. The documentation wasn't clear, and I had to redo it three times. Lost almost a full sprint on that story alone.\"\n   579→\n   580→Charlie (Senior Dev): _defensive_ \"Hold on - I wrote those migration docs, and they were perfectly clear. The issue was that the requirements kept changing mid-story!\"\n   581→\n   582→Alice (Product Owner): _frustrated_ \"That's not fair, Charlie. We only clarified requirements once, and that was because the technical team didn't ask the right questions during planning!\"\n   583→\n   584→Charlie (Senior Dev): _heat rising_ \"We asked plenty of questions! You said the schema was finalized, then two days into development you wanted to add three new fields!\"\n   585→\n   586→Bob (Scrum Master): _intervening calmly_ \"Let's take a breath here. This is exactly the kind of thing we need to unpack.\"\n   587→\n   588→Bob (Scrum Master): \"Elena, you spent almost a full sprint on Story {{difficult_story_num}}. Charlie, you're saying requirements changed. Alice, you feel the right questions weren't asked up front.\"\n   589→\n   590→Bob (Scrum Master): \"{user_name}, you have visibility across the whole project. What's your take on this situation?\"\n   591→</output>\n   592→\n   593→<action>WAIT for {user_name} to respond and help facilitate the conflict resolution</action>\n   594→\n   595→<action>Use {user_name}'s response to guide the discussion toward systemic understanding rather than blame</action>\n   596→\n   597→<output>\n   598→Bob (Scrum Master): [Synthesizes {user_name}'s input with what the team shared] \"So it sounds like the core issue was {{root_cause_based_on_discussion}}, not any individual person's fault.\"\n   599→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017HTAduJyEY5nnXzS9Qtj1F","session_id":"eb26302c-c52a-41c7-9204-5eb8c12a854c","uuid":"3e28fdc2-66ec-4fcb-b65a-a5a576cab50e","timestamp":"2026-03-21T11:36:30.222Z"}
