{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YNMsaGGR4GStNtBGnKEAEY","type":"tool_result","content":"1328-\n1329-1. **4-phase pipeline (create, dev, review, verify) works.** 17 bugs caught across the day, with verify catching integration seam issues that review missed (AC10 warning propagation). Both phases earn their cost.\n1330-2. **Session issues log as single source of truth.** Having every subagent write to `.session-issues.md` made 8 retrospectives fast and accurate. This pattern is non-negotiable.\n1331:3. **AC expansion at story creation.** Going from epic-level ACs (3-4 per story) to story-level ACs (6-10 per story) gave granular verification targets and caught integration gaps earlier.\n1332-4. **Lightweight stories complete in single automation runs.** Stories 5-1 and 5-2 ran through ralph's full pipeline in ~17-20 minutes each. Well-scoped stories with clear ACs are ideal automation candidates.\n1333-5. **Rebuild Docker image before re-verification.** The 4-1 AC10 \"PARTIAL PASS\" was caused by a stale Docker image. Always rebuild when re-verifying after code changes.\n1334-\n--\n1408-**Recommendation for next sprint:**\n1409-1. Dedicate the first session to tech debt: fix verify-env patches, readPatchFile path resolution, tree-shaking issue, and BATS tests. These 4 items are genuine blockers or quality gaps.\n1410-2. Reduce retro frequency to 2 per day max (mid-day checkpoint + end-of-day consolidation). Eight retros created more overhead than value.\n1411:3. Before starting Epic 6 or 7, ensure the verification infrastructure actually works for patch-modifying and export-dependent stories. Otherwise those stories will hit the same blockers.\n1412-\n1413----\n1414-\n--\n1416-\n1417-**Sprint:** Operational Excellence Sprint\n1418-**Session window:** ~07:55Z – ~11:01Z (approx 3 hours)\n1419:**Sprint progress:** 20/25 stories done (80%), Epics 0-5 complete, Epic 6 in progress\n1420-**Generated:** 2026-03-21T14:45Z\n1421-\n1422----\n--\n1430-| 0-3-run-command-dashboard | verify | done | Minor format deviations accepted |\n1431-| 0-5-1-stream-json-claude-driver | verify | done | Clean pass, no issues |\n1432-| 0-5-2-stream-event-parser | verify | done | Export fix required, then 6/6 ACs passed |\n1433:| 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec | create-story | done | Story created from UX spec |\n1434:| 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec | dev-story | done | 3-file split, Ink components rewritten |\n1435:| 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec | code-review | done | 2 HIGH bugs, 1 MEDIUM bug found & fixed |\n1436:| 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec | verify | in progress | Currently verifying |\n1437-\n1438:This session verified 5 stories that were pending from earlier sessions and pushed story 6-1 through create, dev, and code review. High throughput session.\n1439-\n1440----\n1441-\n--\n1446-| Bug | Severity | Story | Status |\n1447-|-----|----------|-------|--------|\n1448-| `parseRalphStatus()` missing new fields from story 0-1 | MEDIUM | 0-1 | Fixed |\n1449:| `updateSprintState()` wiped accumulated `totalCost` every 5s polling | HIGH | 6-1 | Fixed in review |\n1450:| `startsWith` key comparison caused false story matches (e.g., `3-2` matching `3-20`) | MEDIUM | 6-1 | Fixed in review |\n1451-| `parseStreamLine` not exported from `src/index.ts` | MEDIUM | 0-5-2 | Fixed |\n1452-\n1453-### Workarounds Applied (Tech Debt Introduced)\n--\n1455-| Workaround | Story | Risk |\n1456-|------------|-------|------|\n1457-| Container requires `VITEST=1` env var to suppress CLI auto-parse on module import | 0-5-2 | LOW — fragile, couples test env to implementation detail |\n1458:| NFR9 300-line limit forced 3-file split with indirection (`ink-app.tsx` / `ink-components.tsx` / `ink-activity-components.tsx`) | 6-1 | LOW — adds navigation complexity but avoids circular deps |\n1459:| Cost from early events before `sprintInfo` init is silently lost | 6-1 | MEDIUM — cost display may undercount |\n1460:| `run.ts` at 308 lines (8 over 300-line NFR9 limit) | 6-1 | LOW — pre-existing, not addressed |\n1461-\n1462-### Verification Gaps\n1463-\n--\n1466-| VictoriaLogs returned zero events for `codeharness progress` — no structured logging | 0-1 | Observability blind spot for progress command |\n1467-| VictoriaLogs returned zero events for `parseStreamLine` — pure function, no telemetry | 0-5-2 | Expected for pure functions, but means no runtime observability |\n1468-| No BATS tests in container (`ralph/tests/` not in npm package) | 0-2 | Verification relies on mock invocation, not integration tests |\n1469:| No integration test for full run-to-renderer-to-component pipeline with cost accumulation across polling cycles | 6-1 | Cost accumulation bugs could regress |\n1470-\n1471-### Code Quality Concerns\n1472-\n1473-- Renderer accumulates cost internally with no external read path. `updateSprintState` has implicit merge behavior — makes testing and debugging harder.\n1474-- `currentIterationCount` in `run.ts` is a mutable closure variable updated from stderr parsing — updates delayed until next 5-second polling interval.\n1475:- Old `epic-6-retrospective.md` documents Brownfield Onboarding epic, not Dashboard Visualization Rework — stale/misleading artifact.\n1476-\n1477-### Tooling/Infrastructure Problems\n1478-\n--\n1486-- **High throughput:** 5 stories verified + 1 story through create/dev/review in a single session.\n1487-- **Code review caught critical bugs:** The `totalCost` wipe bug and `startsWith` false-match bug were both caught before verify — code review proving its value.\n1488-- **Clean verifications:** Story 0-5-1 passed with zero issues. Stories 0-1, 0-2, 0-3 required only minor fixes.\n1489:- **Epic completion:** Epics 0 and 0.5 are now fully done, clearing the path for Epic 6 dashboard rework.\n1490-- **Session issues log working as intended:** Every subagent reported its findings, making this retro possible without guesswork.\n1491-\n1492----\n--\n1495-\n1496-- **Export omission (0-5-2):** `parseStreamLine` was implemented but never exported from `src/index.ts`. This is a recurring pattern — new functions get created but not wired into the public API. Dev phase should include an export check.\n1497-- **Proof format issues (0-2):** Verification initially failed because proof document reused evidence blocks instead of having distinct ones per AC. This is a process friction that wastes verify iterations.\n1498:- **Cost accumulation gap (6-1):** Events arriving before `sprintInfo` is set silently lose their cost data. This was identified but not fixed — it shipped as known tech debt.\n1499-- **Stale artifacts:** The `epic-6-retrospective.md` file contains content from a different epic, which caused confusion during story creation.\n1500-- **No BATS test coverage in container:** This has been flagged in multiple retros and remains unfixed. Ralph tests are excluded from the npm package, so container-based verification cannot run them.\n1501-\n--\n1506-### Patterns to Repeat\n1507-- **Code review before verify** caught 2 HIGH-severity bugs that would have cost multiple verify iterations to diagnose. The 4-phase pipeline is working.\n1508-- **Session issues log** as structured input to retrospectives eliminates guesswork and ensures nothing is forgotten.\n1509:- **Story creation from UX spec** (6-1) produced well-scoped ACs that the dev phase could implement without ambiguity.\n1510-\n1511-### Patterns to Avoid\n1512-- **Skipping export wiring** — new public functions must be added to `src/index.ts` as part of the dev phase, not discovered during verify.\n--\n1520-\n1521-### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n1522-1. **Clean up stale `epic-6-retrospective.md`** — either delete or rename to reflect its actual content (Brownfield Onboarding).\n1523:2. **Complete 6-1 verification** — story is in `verifying` state, needs to finish.\n1524-\n1525-### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)\n1526-3. **Add export-check to dev phase** — any new public function must appear in `src/index.ts` exports. Add this as a checklist item in the dev workflow.\n1527:4. **Fix cost accumulation gap in 6-1** — events before `sprintInfo` init should buffer cost, not discard it.\n1528-5. **Add integration test for cost accumulation across polling cycles** — the cost wipe bug was caught by review, but there is no regression test.\n1529-6. **Refactor `run.ts`** — at 308 lines it exceeds the 300-line NFR9 limit. Extract the iteration counting and stderr parsing.\n1530-\n--\n1557-\n1558-**Sprint:** Operational Excellence Sprint\n1559-**Session window:** ~10:44Z – ~11:30Z (approx 45 minutes, two ralph sessions)\n1560:**Sprint progress:** 21/25 stories done at session start -> 22/25 done at session end (story 6-1 completed)\n1561-**Timestamp:** 2026-03-21T15:10Z\n1562-\n1563----\n--\n1566-\n1567-| Story | Phase | Outcome | Notes |\n1568-|-------|-------|---------|-------|\n1569:| 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec | create-story | Done | Derived from UX spec; no formal epic-6 definition file existed |\n1570:| 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec | dev-story | Done | 3-file split to meet NFR9 300-line limit |\n1571:| 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec | code-review | Done | 2 HIGH/MEDIUM bugs found and fixed |\n1572:| 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec | verify | Done | Static analysis verification in container |\n1573-\n1574:One story attempted, one story completed through all phases. Story 6-1 rewrote Ink dashboard components to match the UX spec, splitting the renderer into `ink-components.tsx`, `ink-activity-components.tsx`, and `ink-app.tsx`.\n1575-\n1576----\n1577-\n--\n1608-|----|-------------|------------|\n1609-| I1 | Shared observability stack port conflict — harness-specific compose tried to start when shared stack already had ports bound | Used shared stack directly |\n1610-| I2 | Stale `codeharness-verify` container from previous session still running | `docker rm -f` before new verification |\n1611:| I3 | `codeharness sync --story 6-1 --direction files-to-beads` failed — \"Story file not found or has no Status line\" | Skipped sync; did not block verification |\n1612:| I4 | Stale `epic-6-retrospective.md` references Brownfield Onboarding epic, not Dashboard Visualization Rework | Not fixed — misleading artifact |\n1613-\n1614----\n1615-\n1616-## 3. What Went Well\n1617-\n1618:- **Story 6-1 completed end-to-end in a single session** — create, dev, code-review, verify all passed.\n1619-- **Code review caught two real bugs (B1, B2)** before verification. The cost-wipe bug (B1) would have been user-visible in production.\n1620-- **File splitting strategy worked** — the 3-file approach satisfied NFR9 and avoided circular imports cleanly.\n1621-- **Story creation handled missing epic definition gracefully** — derived requirements from UX spec and existing code without blocking.\n--\n1627-- **Infrastructure friction consumed time** — port conflicts, stale containers, and sync failures required manual intervention (I1, I2, I3).\n1628-- **No runtime verification** — static analysis of the dist bundle is valid but weaker than actually rendering components. Runtime rendering tests would catch issues that static analysis misses (V1).\n1629-- **Missing artifacts** — AGENTS.md, exec-plan, and proof document were not created during dev-story phase. These are expected by the process but were skipped.\n1630:- **Stale epic-6-retrospective.md is misleading** — references wrong epic content. Anyone reading it will be confused about Epic 6's purpose.\n1631-\n1632----\n1633-\n--\n1652-### Fix Now (before next session)\n1653-\n1654-- [ ] Clean up stale `codeharness-verify` containers (`docker rm -f`)\n1655:- [ ] Delete or update stale `epic-6-retrospective.md` to reflect actual Epic 6 content\n1656-\n1657-### Fix Soon (next sprint)\n1658-"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017HTAduJyEY5nnXzS9Qtj1F","session_id":"eb26302c-c52a-41c7-9204-5eb8c12a854c","uuid":"52aeb6ef-65dc-4