{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QLon84fhsNo4z139Mj7aYb","type":"tool_result","content":"    50→\n    51→- **HIGH bug fixed:** `updateSprintState()` wiped accumulated `totalCost` every 5s during polling — cost display would flash and disappear. Fixed with field preservation.\n    52→- **MEDIUM bug fixed:** `startsWith` key comparison in `StoryBreakdown` caused false matches (e.g., story `3-2` matching `3-20`). Fixed to exact comparison.\n    53→- **LOW unfixed:** `run.ts` is 308 lines (8 over NFR9 300-line limit). Pre-existing.\n    54→- **Coverage gap:** No integration test for full run→renderer→component pipeline with cost accumulation across polling cycles.\n    55→- **Architecture concern:** Renderer accumulates cost internally with no external read path. `updateSprintState` has implicit merge behavior.\n    56→\n    57→---\n    58→\n    59→## Session 3 — Started 2026-03-21T11:04Z\n    60→\n    61→### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — verify (2026-03-21T11:05Z)\n    62→\n    63→- **Infrastructure:** Shared observability stack was already running but `codeharness status --check-docker` reported it as down. Port conflict when harness-specific compose tried to start — shared stack already bound ports. Resolved by using shared stack directly.\n    64→- **Stale container:** Previous session left `codeharness-verify` container running. Had to `docker rm -f` before starting a new one.\n    65→- **Beads sync failure:** `codeharness sync --story 6-1 --direction files-to-beads` failed with \"Story file not found or has no Status line\".\n    66→- **Observation:** Verifier used static analysis of the dist bundle rather than runtime rendering. Valid black-box approach but doesn't test runtime behavior.\n    67→\n    68→---\n    69→\n    70→## Session 4 — Started 2026-03-21T11:14Z\n    71→\n    72→### 6-2-verify-stream-json-pipeline-e2e — create-story (2026-03-21T11:16Z)\n    73→\n    74→- **No epic-6 definition file exists.** Story file already existed with sufficient detail.\n    75→- **Risk: AC5 requires manual verification** with screenshot proof — non-automatable, depends on having a valid story in backlog.\n    76→- **Risk: AC1 references `ralph/logs/` for recorded NDJSON** — ephemeral/gitignored. Fixture needs hand-curation from real log.\n    77→- **Observation:** Last story in Epic 6. Completing it closes the epic.\n    78→\n    79→### 6-2-verify-stream-json-pipeline-e2e — dev-story (2026-03-21T11:20Z)\n    80→\n    81→- **Test file location diverges from story spec**: Story specified `tests/run-pipeline.test.ts` but vitest root is `src/`. Placed at `src/__tests__/run-pipeline.test.ts`.\n    82→- **No real recorded NDJSON logs available**: Fixture constructed synthetically — `ralph/logs/` only has single-line result events, not full stream-json output.\n    83→- **makeLineHandler duplication**: Test reconstructs the handler because it's a closure in `run.ts`, not exported. Could diverge if `run.ts` changes.\n    84→- **AC5 not completable autonomously**: Requires manual `codeharness run` and screenshot capture.\n    85→\n    86→### 6-2-verify-stream-json-pipeline-e2e — code-review (2026-03-21T11:26Z)\n    87→\n    88→- **HIGH fixed:** Test reimplemented production `makeLineHandler` instead of importing it — changes wouldn't be caught. Fixed by extracting `createLineProcessor` to `run-helpers.ts`.\n    89→- **HIGH fixed:** Story File List wrong path. Fixed.\n    90→- **MEDIUM fixed:** `makeLineHandler` not exportable (closure in run.ts). Extracted to run-helpers.ts.\n    91→- **MEDIUM fixed:** Unused `vi` import.\n    92→- **LOW unfixed:** No test for multi-byte UTF-8 split across chunk boundaries.\n    93→- **LOW unfixed:** Renderer state accumulation test uses manual switch, not real Ink renderer.\n    94→- **Coverage gap:** AC5 manual verification still incomplete.\n    95→\n    96→### 6-2-verify-stream-json-pipeline-e2e — verify (2026-03-21T11:33Z)\n    97→\n    98→- **Stale container from previous session:** Had to `docker rm -f codeharness-verify` before starting.\n    99→- **Port conflict with shared stack:** `docker-compose.harness.yml` tried to bind already-used ports. Used shared stack directly."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017HTAduJyEY5nnXzS9Qtj1F","session_id":"eb26302c-c52a-41c7-9204-5eb8c12a854c","uuid":"86f0e230-adda-4852-b9a7-418be8bb3aad","timestamp":"2026-03-21T11:37:25.719Z"}
