{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MmPmN4MSGEYqgPSAbUdZLf","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eb26302c-c52a-41c7-9204-5eb8c12a854c","uuid":"f7109dc1-f581-4278-b01c-c5b9f725f117","timestamp":"2026-03-21T11:40:04.910Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"- **All 4 automatable ACs passed** with 48 total assertions.","newString":"- **All 4 automatable ACs passed** with 48 total assertions.\n\n### epic-6-retrospective (2026-03-21T11:37Z)\n\n- **Epic numbering collision:** Two sprints reused \"Epic 6\" for different epics. Stale retro file persisted across 4+ session retros before being overwritten.\n- **Action item carry-forward rate ~100%:** Retro action items are generated but never executed. Process failure, not documentation gap.\n- **Story 6-1 harder than expected:** NFR9 300-line limit forced 3-file split not anticipated during story creation.\n- **Story 6-2 harder than expected:** `makeLineHandler` was untestable closure — required production refactor to extract `createLineProcessor`.\n- **Known tech debt:** Cost accumulation data loss for events before `sprintInfo` init.","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-21\n\n### 0-1-sprint-state-live-updates — verify (2026-03-21T07:55Z)\n\n- **Bug found and fixed:** `parseRalphStatus()` in `migration.ts` was missing the new `currentStory`, `currentPhase`, `lastAction`, `acProgress` fields added by this story. Migration test was failing. Fixed by adding null defaults to the return object.\n- **Observability gap:** VictoriaLogs returned zero log events for all `codeharness progress` CLI invocations. The progress command doesn't emit structured logs.\n\n### 0-2-ralph-progress-display — verify (2026-03-21T08:00Z)\n\n- **Proof format issue:** AC3 initially reused evidence from AC2 without its own `bash` code block, causing `codeharness verify` to report 3/4 ACs. Fixed by adding a distinct bash block.\n- **No BATS tests in container:** `ralph/tests/` not included in npm package. Verification relied on direct function invocation with mock data.\n- **VictoriaLogs query syntax:** `_stream_id:*` pattern invalid for VictoriaLogs. Used `*` wildcard instead.\n\n### 0-3-run-command-dashboard — verify (2026-03-21T08:04Z)\n\n- **Minor format deviations:** Story specified checkmark/cross prefixes but implementation uses `[OK]`/`[FAIL]` tags. Functionally equivalent, passed verification.\n- **Architecture difference:** Story specified `DashboardFormatter` class but implementation uses Ink React components. Same functionality, different design.\n\n### 0-5-1-stream-json-claude-driver — verify (2026-03-21T08:09Z)\n\n- Clean verification — all 4 ACs passed without issues.\n\n### 0-5-2-stream-event-parser — verify (2026-03-21T10:35Z)\n\n- **Infrastructure fix:** `parseStreamLine` was not exported from `src/index.ts`, making it inaccessible in the container's dist bundle. Added re-export to `src/index.ts` and rebuilt.\n- **ESM import workaround:** Container requires `VITEST=1` env var to suppress CLI auto-parse on module import. Uses `node --input-type=module` for ESM.\n- **[OBSERVABILITY GAP]** VictoriaLogs returned zero log events for all parser invocations — `parseStreamLine` is a pure function with no telemetry.\n- **Non-standard status from previous session:** Sprint status had `verified` (not a valid status). Normalized to `verifying` before proceeding.\n- All 6 ACs passed black-box verification after infrastructure fix.\n\n---\n\n## Session 2 — Started 2026-03-21T10:44Z\n\n### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — create-story (2026-03-21T10:47Z)\n\n- **Ambiguity: No formal epic definition file for Epic 6.** Derived intent from story name, UX spec, and existing code.\n- **Workaround: Cost field source unclear.** Story assumes `result` events contain cost data — needs verification during implementation.\n- **Risk: AC10 snapshot test fragility.** Softened to \"matches spec format structure\" rather than literal character comparison.\n- **Observation:** Old `epic-6-retrospective.md` documents Brownfield Onboarding epic, not Dashboard Visualization Rework — stale/misleading.\n\n### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — dev-story (2026-03-21T10:56Z)\n\n- **Workaround: file split to avoid circular imports** — NFR9 300-line limit forced a 3-file split. `ink-app.tsx` composes `ink-components.tsx` and `ink-activity-components.tsx` to avoid circular deps. Adds indirection.\n- **Cost accumulation edge case** — `result` event cost only accumulates when `state.sprintInfo` is non-null. Cost from early events before sprint state init is lost.\n- **Iteration count delay** — `currentIterationCount` in run.ts is a mutable closure variable, updated from stderr parsing. Iteration count updates are delayed until next 5-second polling interval.\n- **Missing artifacts** — AGENTS.md, exec-plan, and proof document not created (not in story tasks).\n\n### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — code-review (2026-03-21T11:01Z)\n\n- **HIGH bug fixed:** `updateSprintState()` wiped accumulated `totalCost` every 5s during polling — cost display would flash and disappear. Fixed with field preservation.\n- **MEDIUM bug fixed:** `startsWith` key comparison in `StoryBreakdown` caused false matches (e.g., story `3-2` matching `3-20`). Fixed to exact comparison.\n- **LOW unfixed:** `run.ts` is 308 lines (8 over NFR9 300-line limit). Pre-existing.\n- **Coverage gap:** No integration test for full run→renderer→component pipeline with cost accumulation across polling cycles.\n- **Architecture concern:** Renderer accumulates cost internally with no external read path. `updateSprintState` has implicit merge behavior.\n\n---\n\n## Session 3 — Started 2026-03-21T11:04Z\n\n### 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec — verify (2026-03-21T11:05Z)\n\n- **Infrastructure:** Shared observability stack was already running but `codeharness status --check-docker` reported it as down. Port conflict when harness-specific compose tried to start — shared stack already bound ports. Resolved by using shared stack directly.\n- **Stale container:** Previous session left `codeharness-verify` container running. Had to `docker rm -f` before starting a new one.\n- **Beads sync failure:** `codeharness sync --story 6-1 --direction files-to-beads` failed with \"Story file not found or has no Status line\".\n- **Observation:** Verifier used static analysis of the dist bundle rather than runtime rendering. Valid black-box approach but doesn't test runtime behavior.\n\n---\n\n## Session 4 — Started 2026-03-21T11:14Z\n\n### 6-2-verify-stream-json-pipeline-e2e — create-story (2026-03-21T11:16Z)\n\n- **No epic-6 definition file exists.** Story file already existed with sufficient detail.\n- **Risk: AC5 requires manual verification** with screenshot proof — non-automatable, depends on having a valid story in backlog.\n- **Risk: AC1 references `ralph/logs/` for recorded NDJSON** — ephemeral/gitignored. Fixture needs hand-curation from real log.\n- **Observation:** Last story in Epic 6. Completing it closes the epic.\n\n### 6-2-verify-stream-json-pipeline-e2e — dev-story (2026-03-21T11:20Z)\n\n- **Test file location diverges from story spec**: Story specified `tests/run-pipeline.test.ts` but vitest root is `src/`. Placed at `src/__tests__/run-pipeline.test.ts`.\n- **No real recorded NDJSON logs available**: Fixture constructed synthetically — `ralph/logs/` only has single-line result events, not full stream-json output.\n- **makeLineHandler duplication**: Test reconstructs the handler because it's a closure in `run.ts`, not exported. Could diverge if `run.ts` changes.\n- **AC5 not completable autonomously**: Requires manual `codeharness run` and screenshot capture.\n\n### 6-2-verify-stream-json-pipeline-e2e — code-review (2026-03-21T11:26Z)\n\n- **HIGH fixed:** Test reimplemented production `makeLineHandler` instead of importing it — changes wouldn't be caught. Fixed by extracting `createLineProcessor` to `run-helpers.ts`.\n- **HIGH fixed:** Story File List wrong path. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** `makeLineHandler` not exportable (closure in run.ts). Extracted to run-helpers.ts.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Unused `vi` import.\n- **LOW unfixed:** No test for multi-byte UTF-8 split across chunk boundaries.\n- **LOW unfixed:** Renderer state accumulation test uses manual switch, not real Ink renderer.\n- **Coverage gap:** AC5 manual verification still incomplete.\n\n### 6-2-verify-stream-json-pipeline-e2e — verify (2026-03-21T11:33Z)\n\n- **Stale container from previous session:** Had to `docker rm -f codeharness-verify` before starting.\n- **Port conflict with shared stack:** `docker-compose.harness.yml` tried to bind already-used ports. Used shared stack directly.\n- **AC5 genuinely escalated:** Requires human visual judgment of real-time Ink rendering — correctly tagged `integration-required` in story.\n- **All 4 automatable ACs passed** with 48 total assertions.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":99,"oldLines":3,"newStart":99,"newLines":11,"lines":[" - **Port conflict with shared stack:** `docker-compose.harness.yml` tried to bind already-used ports. Used shared stack directly."," - **AC5 genuinely escalated:** Requires human visual judgment of real-time Ink rendering — correctly tagged `integration-required` in story."," - **All 4 automatable ACs passed** with 48 total assertions.","+","+### epic-6-retrospective (2026-03-21T11:37Z)","+","+- **Epic numbering collision:** Two sprints reused \"Epic 6\" for different epics. Stale retro file persisted across 4+ session retros before being overwritten.","+- **Action item carry-forward rate ~100%:** Retro action items are generated but never executed. Process failure, not documentation gap.","+- **Story 6-1 harder than expected:** NFR9 300-line limit forced 3-file split not anticipated during story creation.","+- **Story 6-2 harder than expected:** `makeLineHandler` was untestable closure — required production refactor to extract `createLineProcessor`.","+- **Known tech debt:** Cost accumulation data loss for events before `sprintInfo` init."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
